  "prompt": "How do I know when most of my Instagram followers are online?",
  "response": "Instagram provides insights into when your followers are most active on the platform, which can help you determine the best times to post content. However, this feature is only available for **Instagram Business or Creator accounts**. Here\u2019s how to check when most of your followers are online:\n\n### Steps to Check Follower Activity:\n1. **Switch to a Business or Creator Account** (if you haven\u2019t already):\n   - Go to your profile settings.\n   - Select **Account** > **Switch to Professional Account**.\n   - Choose either Business or Creator and follow the prompts.\n\n2. **Access Insights**:\n   - Go to your profile and tap the menu (three lines) in the top-right corner.\n   - Select **Insights**.\n\n3. **View Follower Activity**:\n   - Scroll down to the **Audience** section.\n   - Tap **Total Followers**.\n   - In the **Most Active Times** section, you\u2019ll see a graph showing the days and times your followers are most active.\n\n   - The graph will display data in hourly blocks, showing which times of day and days of the week your followers are most likely to be online.\n\n### What You\u2019ll Learn:\n- **Days of the Week**: The most active days for your followers.\n- **Times of the Day**: The most active hours for your followers.\n\n### Tips for Using the Data:\n- **Post During Peak Times**: Schedule your posts when the majority of your followers are online to maximize engagement.\n- **Experiment**: Use the data as a starting point, but don\u2019t be afraid to experiment with posting at different times to see what works best for your audience.\n- **Track Performance**: Monitor your posts\u2019 performance to see if the times you\u2019re posting are resulting in higher engagement.\n\nIf you\u2019re using a **personal account**, you won\u2019t have access to this feature, so consider switching to a Business or Creator account to unlock these insights.",
